|WKB                         QUEST OBJECTIVES
|CKB=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=

|YKOEach quest has one or more objectives that must be completed. There
are several types of objectives you may encounter:

|WKBKill|XX0
  |YKODefeat a specific creature, or a number of creatures. Progress
  is tracked automatically as you fight once you have accepted the quest.

  |WKBExample: |YKO"Slay 3 wolves in the Endrael Forest"

|WKBRetrieve|XX0
  |YKOFind and collect one or more items and deliver them to a quest
  master NPC. When you give the item to the NPC, your progress
  is updated.

  |WKBExample: |YKO"Collect 5 alligator teeth from the Hyndor swamp"

|WKBRescue|XX0
  |YKOLocate a captured or stranded NPC and free them. When you find
  the NPC, use the appropriate command (such as |YKBrescue |YKOor
  |YKBfree|YKO) to complete the objective.

  |WKBExample: |YKO"Find and rescue the priest from the mines"

|WKBEscort|XX0
  |YKOGuide an NPC safely from one location to another. Use the
  |YKBescort |YKOcommand to start the journey. The NPC will move on
  their own - stay in the same room and protect them from enemies.
  If the NPC dies or you wander too far away, the objective resets
  and you will need to try again.

  |WKBExample: |YKO"Escort the elf child safely through the forest"

|WKBTracking Progress:|XX0
  |YKOUse |YKBqstatus |YKOat any time to see how many objectives you have
  completed and how much remains across your accepted quests. When all
  objectives for a quest are finished, the quest completes automatically
  and you receive your rewards.

|CKB=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=
